{meta: artist Jim and Jesse}
{meta: composer Karen Fairchild, Kimberly Schlapman}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Oh the church in the valley oh that little white [C]church
[G]Is the place I love so [D7]well
[G]Now I'm sad and lonely yes I'm sad and [C]lonely
[G]For that little [D7]white church in the [G]dell
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
There's a little white church in the valley
[C]That stands in my memory each [G]day
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
And it seems I can hear the bells ringing
[A7]Though I am many miles [D7]away
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[G]And many times on Sunday morning
[C]The whole countryside would gather [G]there
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
They would all kneel down by the altar
[D7]As they lifted up their voices in [G]prayer
{end_of_verse}

