{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
They would sing the old song Rock of Ages
[C]Oh Christ let me hide myself in [G]Thee
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
And I know some of them are now waiting
[A7]Just o'er the dark and stormy [D7]sea
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
[G]I know their troubles all are ended
[C]And happy forever they will [G]be
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
They are waiting and watching up yonder
[D7]For the coming home of you and [G]me
{end_of_verse}

